integrated national dementia strategic plan to guide the overall effort to 
improve dementia care in the country. It is vital to design and develop a 
national dementia plan in line with a framework outlined by the 2017 World 
Health Organization (WHO) global action plan. The health, social, and economic 
burden from dementia is expected to be high to the developing countries such as 
Ethiopia unless clear prevention and management strategies are designed at a 
national level to cascade the care to the primary care level. The planned 
strategic policy may focus on improving the knowledge and skills of health care 
professionals. Translation and cultural adaptation of cognitive, functional, and 
behavioral assessment batteries is of paramount importance in improving the 
diagnostic accuracy along with availability of advanced imaging, biomarkers, and 
dementia treatment.

